-- Australia shares close lower on plunging oil price, but jobs data offsets
-- By Byron Kaye
-- Thu Dec 11, 2014 12:29AM EST
-- None



SYDNEY, Dec 11 (Reuters) - Australian shares pared most of their heavy early losses on Thursday as investors looked past plunging oil prices and focused on better-than-expected local jobs data. [ID:nL3N0TV17Y]

After falling up to 1.3 percent in early trading, the S&P/ASX 200 index <.AXJO> closed down 0.53 percent or 28.00 points at 5231.0, its third consecutive decline.